==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tractrix
<hw>Tract"rix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Tractor</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A curve such that the
part of the tangent between the point of tangency and a given straight
line is constant; -- so called because it was conceived as described by
the motion of one end of a tangent line as the other end was drawn along
the given line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trad</ent>⟦br⟧
